287431d4-a2c5-472a-aa2e-c884e72dba79.07a2ba92-2c4c-4c25-91ef-1a9cc6253881.prompt=User Identifier 287431d4-a2c5-472a-aa2e-c884e72dba79.1994300e-7c85-4046-bbde-06514c8796be.prompt=Process Instance ID 287431d4-a2c5-472a-aa2e-c884e72dba79.8838809e-0fa7-42f3-a539-3731474d6a5b.prompt=User Identifier 287431d4-a2c5-472a-aa2e-c884e72dba79.9e8bfff7-b832-4434-b5cc-599f9c669c06.description=
Creates a new inventory folder in a Datacenter as seen in vCenter "Inventory > VMs and Templates" view.

Inputs\:
    host - VMware vCenter host hostname or IP.
    user - VMware username.
    password - VMware user's password.
    port - Port to connect on.
Examples\: 443, 80
    protocol - Connection protocol.
Valid values\: "https", "http"
    closeSession - Close the internally kept VMware Infrastructure API session at completion of operation.
    vmDatacenter - Datacenter to create new VM inventory folder in.
    vmFolder - Path of VM inventory folder to create.  Folder names are delimited by a forward slash "/". Will create any parent folders if they do not already exist.  This input is case sensitive.
Example\: /Hewlett Packard Enterprise/Operations Orchestration/Templates

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed successfully.
    failure - Something went wrong.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output.  Descriptive result of the operation.  Reason for error on failure.
    folderID - The ID of the created folder.
